Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Chop the @sweet potato{2} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with the @Mexican style spice mix{1%packet}, @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pop the pepper, onion and half the garlic onto another baking tray. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat.

Roast on the middle shelf of your oven until soft and slightly charred, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While everything roasts, zest and halve the @lime{1}. Halve the @avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the flesh onto a #board{}, then chop into 1cm chunks.

Pop the avocado into a large #bowl{} with lime zest, juice, @honey{15%ml} and @olive oil{2%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set aside.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop into a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}, halve lengthways, then thinly slice widthways.

When 5 mins of cooking time remain, tear the @ciabatta{1} into 2cm chunks and pop into another bowl.

Drizzle with oil, then season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and the remaining garlic. Toss to coat.

Add the croutons and @bacon lardons{90%g} to the sweet potato tray and bake until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}.

When everything is ready, add the roasted sweet potato, pepper, onion, croutons, sliced baby gem into the avocado bowl and mix well.

Share the salad between your bowls, then crumble over the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g} to finish. Enjoy!

> Step 5 MOD: If you've chosen to add bacon lardons to your meal, add them with the croutons to the baking tray and continued as instructed. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook lardons thoroughly.